.TH "blkcg_conf_open_bdev" 9 "blkcg_conf_open_bdev" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
blkcg_conf_open_bdev \- parse and open bdev for per-blkg config update
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct block_device *" blkcg_conf_open_bdev
.BI "(char **inputp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inputp" 12
input string pointer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Parse the device node prefix part, MAJ:MIN, of per-blkg config update
from \fIinput\fP and get and return the matching bdev.  *\fIinputp\fP is
updated to point past the device node prefix.  Returns an \fBERR_PTR\fP
value on error.

Use this function iff \fBblkg_conf_prep\fP can't be used for some reason.
